The number of declared Covid-19 cases in Kenya has risen by 230 to 98,184, Health Cabinet Secretary Mutahi has announced.
CS Kagwe reported Saturday that the new infections were found after analysis of 6,515 samples over the past 24 hours.
This raised the total number of samples tested in the country since the first infection in March to 1,088,378.



